                        <h2>TOEFL Pattern 2024: Home Edition & Test Center</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <table>
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Aspect</th>
                                        <th>TOEFL Home Edition (Online)</th>
                                        <th>TOEFL on Computer (Test Center)</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Test Delivery</td>
                                        <td>The entire exam is taken remotely from home or any location with a stable internet connection.</td>
                                        <td>Taken at an official test center on a computer.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Test Environment</td>
                                        <td>You take the test in a quiet, private location (home or another suitable place).</td>
                                        <td>You take the test in a secure, monitored test center.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Test Format</td>
                                        <td>Computer-based format for Reading, Listening, Speaking, and Writing.</td>
                                        <td>Computer-based format for Reading, Listening, and Writing; Speaking test is face-to-face with an examiner.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Speaking Test</td>
                                        <td>Via video call with an examiner, conducted remotely.</td>
                                        <td>In-person with a real examiner in the test center.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Availability</td>
                                        <td>Available on specific dates, offering more flexibility in terms of location and scheduling.</td>
                                        <td>Available on fixed dates at designated test centers.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Result Availability</td>
                                        <td>Results are available within 6 days.</td>
                                        <td>Results are available within 10-13 days.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Test Duration</td>
                                        <td>The same as the standard TOEFL exam, 3 hours.</td>
                                        <td>Same duration of 3 hours.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Cost</td>
                                        <td>The cost is typically similar to the test center version but may vary depending on location.</td>
                                        <td>The cost is generally the same as the online format, though there may be slight regional differences.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Test Security</td>
                                        <td>Identity verification and test security measures are taken online. Requires a computer with a webcam, microphone, and a stable internet connection.</td>
                                        <td>In-person identity verification at the test center, strict monitoring during the test.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
