                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>TOEFL Preparation Tips 2024</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <table>
                                <thead>
                                    <tr>
                                        <th>Preparation Aspect</th>
                                        <th>Details</th>
                                    </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Understand the Test Format</td>
                                        <td>Familiarize yourself with the TOEFL structure: Reading, Listening, Speaking, and Writing. Each section has its own format, rules, and timing.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Practice Regularly</td>
                                        <td>Regular practice is essential. Take mock tests, practice speaking with a partner, and work on reading and writing under timed conditions.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Build Vocabulary</td>
                                        <td>Improve your English vocabulary, especially academic terms and phrases commonly used in TOEFL tasks.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Improve Time Management</td>
                                        <td>Practice managing your time effectively. Each section has a strict time limit, and pacing yourself is key to completing all tasks.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                    <tr>
                                        <td>Seek Feedback</td>
                                        <td>Take practice tests and seek feedback from teachers, peers, or native speakers, especially for speaking and writing, to identify areas for improvement.</td>
                                    </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </table>
                        </div>
