                    <div class="content-section">
                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>
                        <div class="highlight-box">
                            <h3>What is the best way of preparing for the TOEFL test?</h3>
                            <p>There are innumerable official prep offerings. These are insights-driven, accessible, and can be personalized. Apart from this, there are various TOEFL guides and books (both online and offline), practice test materials, and other items for TOEFL test preparations.</p>
                            <h3>For the listening test, can I wear earbuds or headphones during the test?</h3>
                            <p>Personal earbuds and headphones are not allowed in a TOEFL test center. For the listening test, you will be given headphones at the test center. For the TOEFL iBT Home Edition, you have to use your computer speaker as no earbuds and headphones are allowed.</p>
                            <h3>Is taking notes permissible during the TOEFL test?</h3>
                            <p>Yes, you can take notes for the speaking and listening sections particularly, in the TOEFL test. There are different rules about the note-taking materials that you can use depending on whether you are taking the test at home or at a test center.</p>
                            <h3>I could not finish the TOEFL test due to some technical problem. What to do then?</h3>
                            <p>You have to contact TOEFL services if you have not received any instructions about the next steps that you have to take. You will have to find the TOEFL services contact information for the country from where you are appearing for your test.</p>
                            <h3>What is the validity of the TOEFL test scores?</h3>
                            <p>TOEFL scores are valid for 2 years from the date of the test. ETS does not report or send scores after 2 years.</p>
                        </div>
